<ul><li><cite id="CITEREFBritannica_Holodomor" class="citation encyclopaedia cs1">Makuch, Andrij. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.britannica.com/place/Ukraine/History#ref404577">"The famine of 1932–1933"</a>. <i>Encyclopædia Britannica online</i>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20151123082312/https://www.britannica.com/place/Ukraine/History#ref404577">Archived</a> from the original on 23 November 2015<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2 November</span> 2015</span>. <q>The Great Famine (Holodomor) of 1932–1933 – a man-made demographic catastrophe unprecedented in peacetime. Of the estimated six to eight million people who died in the Soviet Union, about four to five million were Ukrainians&#160;... Its deliberate nature is underscored by the fact that no physical basis for famine existed in Ukraine&#160;... Soviet authorities set requisition quotas for Ukraine at an impossibly high level. Brigades of special agents were dispatched to Ukraine to assist in procurement, and homes were routinely searched and foodstuffs confiscated&#160;... The rural population was left with insufficient food to feed itself.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=The+famine+of+1932%E2%80%931933&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclop%C3%A6dia+Britannica+online&amp;rft.aulast=Makuch&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrij&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fplace%2FUkraine%2FHistory%23ref404577&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMass+killings+under+communist+regimes" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFMace1986" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_Mace" title="James Mace">Mace, James</a> (1986). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/famineinukraine100serb">"The man-made famine of 1933 in Soviet Ukraine"</a>. In Serbyn, Roman; <a href="/wiki/Bohdan_Krawchenko" title="Bohdan Krawchenko">Krawchenko, Bohdan</a> (eds.). <i>Famine in Ukraine in 1932–1933</i>. Canada: <a href="/wiki/Canadian_Institute_of_Ukrainian_Studies" class="mw-redirect" title="Canadian Institute of Ukrainian Studies">Canadian Institute of Ukrainian Studies</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780092862434" title="Special:BookSources/9780092862434"><bdi>9780092862434</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=The+man-made+famine+of+1933+in+Soviet+Ukraine&amp;rft.btitle=Famine+in+Ukraine+in+1932%E2%80%931933&amp;rft.place=Canada&amp;rft.pub=Canadian+Institute+of+Ukrainian+Studies&amp;rft.date=1986&amp;rft.isbn=9780092862434&amp;rft.aulast=Mace&amp;rft.aufirst=James&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Ffamineinukraine100serb&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMass+killings+under+communist+regimes" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFLemkin2008" class="citation book cs1">Lemkin, Raphael (2008) [1953]. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120302234607/http://www.uccla.ca/SOVIET_GENOCIDE_IN_THE_UKRAINE.pdf">"Soviet Genocide in the Ukraine"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. In Luciuk, Lubomyr; Grekul, Lisa (eds.). <i>Holodomor: Reflections on the Great Famine of 1932–1933 in Soviet Ukraine</i>. Kashtan Press. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1896354330" title="Special:BookSources/978-1896354330"><bdi>978-1896354330</bdi></a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.uccla.ca/SOVIET_GENOCIDE_IN_THE_UKRAINE.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> on 2 March 2012<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">22 July</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Soviet+Genocide+in+the+Ukraine&amp;rft.btitle=Holodomor%3A+Reflections+on+the+Great+Famine+of+1932%E2%80%931933+in+Soviet+Ukraine&amp;rft.pub=Kashtan+Press&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=978-1896354330&amp;rft.aulast=Lemkin&amp;rft.aufirst=Raphael&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.uccla.ca%2FSOVIET_GENOCIDE_IN_THE_UKRAINE.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMass+killings+under+communist+regimes" class="Z3988"></span></li></ul>
